The LPGA Tour will resume in July after being temporarily stopped by the coronavirus pandemic. The 2020 season will restart in Ohio on 31 July, with the three-day Drive on Championship at Inverness Club, Toledo. That will be followed by the Marathon LPGA Classic from 6 August, with spectators allowed on site at Highland Meadows Golf Club, Sylvania. South Korea’s Inbee Park won the Australian Open in February, which was the final LPGA event before lockdown. A number of LPGA events have been rescheduled, with the US Women’s Open set to take place in December.